===Noun Phrase===
'''whole number'''

A [[non-negative]] [[integer]]; a member of the infinite sequence {0, 1, 2, 3, ...}.

''Since the amount was less than half, and a '''whole number''' was required, the result was 0.''

===Usage Note===
The whole numbers are ''countable'' or ''denumerable'', the set having size [[aleph-null]].

